-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
---|   USER MANUAL (v2.6)   |---
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=

--- PLAYER COMMANDS ---

1. /register
   Command: /register <password> <password> [captcha]
   Description: Registers a new account.
   Note: If Captcha is enabled, enter the code displayed in chat as the 3rd argument.

2. /login
   Command: /login <password>
   Description: Logs the player into their account.

3. /changepass
   Command: /changepass <old password> <new password> <new password>
   Description: Allows a logged-in player to change their password.

4. /premium
   Command: /premium
   Description: Verifies your account with Mojang. If successful, enables Auto-Login
   for future connections (skips password).

5. /cracked
   Command: /cracked
   Description: Disables Auto-Login. You will be required to enter your password
   every time you join.

--- ADMIN COMMANDS (Permission: pureauth.admin) ---

6. /pureauth
   Command: /pureauth
   Description: Displays the help menu with all available subcommands.

7. /pureauth reload
   Command: /pureauth reload
   Description: Reloads the configuration (messages, settings, and database connection).

8. /pureauth unregister
   Command: /pureauth unregister <player>
   Description: Completely deletes a player's account from the database.

9. /pureauth register
   Command: /pureauth register <player> <password>
   Description: Manually registers an account for a player (useful for bedrock/console players).

10. /pureauth forcelogin
    Command: /pureauth forcelogin <player>
    Description: Forcefully logs in a player, bypassing password and lock checks.

11. /pureauth unlock
    Command: /pureauth unlock <player>
    Description: Unblocks an account that was locked due to too many failed login attempts.
    Note: This will kick the player to reset their login state.

12. /pureauth setpassword
    Command: /pureauth setpassword <player> <new password>
    Description: Administratively changes a player's password (does not require the old one).

13. /pureauth info
    Command: /pureauth info <player>
    Description: Displays advanced info: Registration IP, Last IP, Premium Status, Lock Status, and Kick Count.

14. /pureauth accounts
    Command: /pureauth accounts <IP>
    Description: Lists all usernames registered to a specific IP address.

15. /pureauth location
    Command: /pureauth location <login|register>
    Description: Sets the global teleport points.
    - 'login': Spawn for unauthenticated registered players.
    - 'register': Spawn for new players.

16. /pureauth stats
    Command: /pureauth stats
    Description: [CONSOLE ONLY] Displays a full technical report of the plugin status and settings.

--- SYSTEM NOTES ---

- Premium Auto-Login: Requires ProtocolLib. Uses UUID Spoofing to ensure
  inventory data is saved under the Offline UUID, preventing item loss.
- Account Locking: By default, 3 kicks (9 wrong passwords) will lock an account.
- Safe Mode: If enabled in config, admin commands listed above will be blocked
  in-game and can only be used from the Console.

The plugin is for Minecraft version 1.21.X (Paper). JDK-21.
Developed by SzymeX Dev Studio.
